            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@3N4N Thank you for your notification. I can reproduce it with following the `shell-powershell` guidance or `set shell=cmd.exe`. Also, it can be triggered in the prerelease build (`NVIM v0.8.0-dev+578-gca64b589c`). I also reproduced it on another machine.\r\n\r\nIf possible, you can try repeating the window close-reopen operation for more times. For me, this bug can be steadily triggered after 2 repetitions.\r\n\r\nMoreover, **in these cases, this issue will not be triggered:**\r\n- closing the terminal window by hand,\r\n- mimicing human operation by adding blocking code in key mapping (as mentioned above),\r\n- or leaving another window with the same terminal buffer opened, which means if the buffer can be observed, it will not collapse, like, ah, Schrodinger's buffer.\r\n",
