            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Confirming that I can reproduce the issue, but only after the second close-reopen. And it happens with both pwsh and cmd. So the repro effectively is:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nnvim --clean\r\n:tmap <silent> <space>t <C-\\><C-n>:q<CR>\r\n:tabnew | terminal\r\nidir<CR><space>t\r\n:tabnew | b2\r\ni<space>t\r\n:tabnew | b2\r\ni  \" here is where the terminal buffer jumps from bottom to close to the top\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n**Update**: In WSL Ubuntu, the same happens when using the Windows shells (pwsh.exe/cmd.exe) as `:set shell`. But when I use Linux's pwsh, which is installed in Linux, it doesn't happen.",
